03/10/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government approved the draft national strategy against poverty on Thursday (2 October). Labour and Social Policy Minister Hristina Hristova said the document covers the period 2003-2006 and is designed to reduce the number of people living on social welfare by 100,000. In addition, the programme aims to increase the minimum wage and social benefits, while cutting unemployment.
In other news Thursday, Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov met in Baghdad with Patrick Kennedy, a senior US official in Iraq. Kennedy praised the performance of the Bulgarian peacekeeping unit in Karbala. (24 Chassa, Standart - 03/10/03; BTA, BNR, BNT - 02/10/03)
